==A==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=actual extension}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#measured extension|measured extension]]''.}}

{{term|1=anchor}}
{{term|1=anchorage|multi=y}}
{{defn|1=A rigid component, commonly constructed of cast iron, located at the end of a tendon and that directly transfers a tendon's force to the surrounding concrete.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|3–4}}<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|30}} }}

{{term|1=anchor block}}
{{defn|1=A rigid, usually circular, component placed over a bundle of prestressing strands at the end of a tendon, and that transfers the strand forces directly to the anchor component via tapered wedges located within its internal conical recess.<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|32}}}}

{{term|1=anchor centreline height}}
{{defn|1=The positional dimension setting the height of an end-anchorage, usually measured vertically up from the formwork surface to the mid-depth of the anchor component.}}

{{term|1=anchor friction}}
{{defn|1=The loss of prestressing force in the tendons due to friction generated by the strands sliding against the anchorage assembly during the tensioning operations.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|4}} }}

{{term|1=anchor recess}}
{{defn|1=A formwork blockout or recess former fitted to the edge formwork of a post-tensioned concrete member, and that creates a temporary void space external to the prestressing anchor to allow the anchor block or similar to be fitted after formwork stripping.<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|32}}}}

{{term|1=anchor set}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#wedge set|wedge set]]''.}}

{{term|1=anchorage assembly}}
{{defn|1=An assembly of components located at the end of a tendon and commonly comprising any employed combination of the anchor, anchor block, banana block, barrels, wedges, ducting transition, grouting tubes and anti-burst reinforcement.<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|30–32}} }}

{{term|1=anchorage zone}}
{{defn|1=The region at the end of a tendon in the immediate vicinity of the anchorage, in which the most concentrated force transfer occurs between the anchor and the surrounding concrete.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|4}} }}

{{term|1=anti-burst reinforcement}}
{{defn|1=Unstressed reinforcement provided in the anchorage zones around individual tendons and/or grouped anchorages, which resists the secondary stresses created in the concrete from the applied prestressing forces.<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|20}} }}

{{glossary end}}

==B==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=banana}}
{{term|1=banana block|multi=y}}
{{defn|1=A short, curved anchor block sometimes fitted to a mono-strand stressed tendon, and that transfers the strand forces to the anchor via tapered wedges located within its internal conical recesses. }}

{{term|1=bar}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#threaded bar|threaded bar]]''.}}

{{term|1=barrel}}
{{defn|1=A cylindrical component fitted over a single prestressing strand at an anchorage, and that transfers the strand force to the anchor via tapered wedges located within its internal conical recess. A set of barrels can be used with a mono-strand stressed tendon as an alternative to an anchor block.}}

{{term|1=block}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#anchor block|anchor block]]''.}}

{{term|1=bond |2=[[adhesion|bond]]}}
{{defn|1=The adhesion of concrete or grout to prestressing strands, wires or bars, or to unstressed reinforcement, either through friction or mechanical interlock.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|9}} }}

{{term|1=bond strength |2=[[bond strength]]}}
{{defn|1=The resistance to separation of hardened concrete or grout from prestressing strands, wires or bars, or from unstressed reinforcement. Typically measured in the same units as concrete compressive strength.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|9}} }}

{{term|1=bonded length}}
{{defn|1=The length of that part of a prestressing tendon that is, or is to be, bonded to the surrounding concrete, either directly or via internal grouting of the tendon's ducting.}}

{{term|1=bonded tendon}}
{{term|1=bonded prestressing|multi=y 2=[[Prestressed concrete#Bonded post-tensioning|bonded prestressing]]}}
{{defn|1=A prestressing tendon that is, or is to be, permanently connected to the surrounding concrete along the full length between its end anchorages. Such connection may be directly, or via internal grouting of the tendon's ducting.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|9}}}}

{{term|1=bripak}}
{{defn|1=A portable frame structure commonly employed on site to support coils of prestressing strand and to facilitate the safe ''unloading'' of continuous lengths of strand into tendons or ducting.}}

{{term|1=bursting stresses}}
{{defn|1=Localised stresses produced by prestressing forces in the anchorage zone of a prestressed member, and that tend to promote tensile rupture in the region immediately inboard of the anchorage.<ref name="LinTY"/>{{rp|279}}}}

{{glossary end}}

==C==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=cable |2=[[wire rope|cable]]}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon|tendon]]''.}}

{{term|1=cable stay}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#stay cable|stay cable]]''.}}

{{term|1=circular prestressing}}
{{defn|1=An arrangement of prestressing where the tendons form partial or full sections of (usually horizontal and circular) arcs between end anchorages. Commonly used for the prestressing of tanks, silos and pipes.<ref name="LinTY"/>{{rp|467–474}} }}

{{term|1=conventional reinforcement |2=[[rebar|conventional reinforcement]]}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#unstressed reinforcement|unstressed reinforcement]]''. }}

{{term|1=coupler}}
{{defn|1=A rigid component, commonly constructed from cast iron, which is located at the end of a tendon and transfers the tendon force from the end of one tendon segment to another.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|19}}<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|27}} }}

{{term|1=cut-off}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon cut-off|tendon cut-off]]''. }}

{{glossary end}}

==D==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=de-bond}}
{{defn|1=Prevent the bond of a prestressing tendon to the surrounding concrete.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|20}}}}

{{term|1=de-bonded length}}
{{defn|1=The length of that part of a prestressing tendon that is to remain permanently unbonded from the surrounding concrete.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|20}}}}

{{term|1=dead end anchorage}}
{{defn|1=A "passive" end anchorage of a prestressing tendon that does not have any jacking operations undertaken at that end.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|20}}<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|20,26}} }}

{{term|1=de-stress}}
{{defn|1=To release the prestressing forces within a tendon, usually in a controlled manner.}}

{{term|1=deviation point}}
{{term|1=deviator|multi=y}}
{{defn|1=A device or structural element that permanently deviates a tendon's profile at a location, for the purposes of producing a reactionary force against the concrete when the tendon is stressed. Used in pre-tensioned elements, and in external prestressing.}}

{{term|1=drape}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon drape|tendon drape]]''.}}

{{term|1=draped tendon}}
{{defn|1=Tendons that are profiled predominately to a curved profile between support points.}}

{{term|1=draw-in}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#wedge draw-in|wedge draw-in]]''. }}

{{term|1=duct}}
{{term|1=ducting |multi=y}}
{{defn|1=Encapsulating tube-like component, usually constructed from galvanised steel or polythene, which creates a void space within the concrete and surrounds the strands, wires or bar of a post-tensioned tendon.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|23}} }}

{{term|1=duct chair}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon chair|tendon chair]]''. }}

{{term|1=duct friction}}
{{defn|1=The stress loss in a prestressing tendon resulting from friction between the tendon and duct during tensioning.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|31}} }}

{{term|1=duct joiner}}
{{defn|1=A component that securely connects separate segments of post tensioning ducting, commonly used when joining precast concrete segments in a prestressed structure. }}

{{term|1=dummy strand}}
{{defn|1=A short length of prestressing strand pre-installed into ducting during concreting to maintain duct integrity. Occasionally used at some jointing arrangements.}}
{{glossary end}}

==E==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=eccentricity}}
{{defn|1=The distance between the centre of gravity of the concrete cross-section and the centroid of its prestressing element(s), at any point along the member.<ref name="PTI"/>{{rp|27}} }}

{{term|1=elastic modulus}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#Young's Modulus|Young's Modulus]]''. }}

{{term|1=elongation}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon extension|tendon extension]]''.}}

{{term|1=end block}}
{{defn|1=An end section of a prestressed member that houses one or more anchorage assemblies, and is often locally enlarged to reduce the applied anchorage stresses.<ref name="LinTY"/>{{rp|278}} }}

{{term|1=extension}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon extension|tendon extension]]''. }}

{{term|1=external post-tensioning}}
{{defn|1=Post-tensioning comprising tendons placed externally to the concrete structure, but connected to it at the end anchorages and profile-deviation points.}}

{{glossary end}}

==F==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=final stress}}
{{defn|1=The final tensioning operation undertaken during post-tensioning, resulting in the design prestress level being established within the member.<ref name="PTIA-1"/>{{rp|1}} }}

{{term|1=flat duct}}
{{defn|1=Ducting with an oval or "stadium" cross sectional shape. Such ducting is usually extruded (if plastic), or constructed from flat metal strip folded and joined with a longitudinal seam. Commonly used for mono-strand bonded tendons.<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|29}}}}

{{term|1=flat tendon}}
{{defn|1=A prestressing tendon installed with no vertical or horizontal curvature. It forms a straight line between end anchorages.}}

{{term|1=friction loss}}
{{defn|1=The loss of prestressing force in a tendon resulting from all frictional sources. The total friction loss in a tendon is the sum of duct friction loss and anchor friction loss.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|31}}<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|11}} }}

{{term|1=full prestressing}}
{{defn|1=Prestressing to a stress level such that, under design loads, no tensile stresses exist in the precompressed tensile zone of the member. Can be compared to ''partial prestressing''.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|45}}<ref name="LinTY"/>{{rp|325}} }}

{{glossary end}}

==G==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=grouting}}
{{defn|1=The process of filling post-tensioning ducts with grout after tensioning.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|32}} }}

{{term|1=grout tube}}
{{defn|1=Tubular components connected to anchors or ducting through which grout is pumped and/or air is bled, during the process of grouting.<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|30}} }}
{{glossary end}}

==H==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=harped tendon}}
{{defn|1=Tendons that are profiled predominately having lengths of straight tendon between points of significant angular deviation. Commonly employed in pre-tensioned elements, where the angular deviations are created by hold-down points in the casting bed.<ref>{{cite web|title=BridgeTalk Discussion Forum|url=http://www.bridgesite.com/dcforum_8z/DCForumID1/1484.html|accessdate=14 September 2016}}</ref> }}

{{term|1=high point}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon high point|tendon high point]]''.}}

{{term|1=hoop tendon}}
{{defn|1=A horizontally-curved tendon forming part or all of a circle, typically installed in vertically-spaced layers up the height of a prestressed tank or silo to resist hoop tensions generated by the stored contents.<ref name="LinTY"/>{{rp|469}} }}
{{glossary end}}

==I==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=initial stress}}
{{defn|1=The first tensioning operation undertaken during post-tensioning, typically applied as soon as the concrete at the anchorage locations has attained sufficient strength to resist the resulting anchorage zone stresses.<ref name="PTIA-1"/>{{rp|1}}}}
{{glossary end}}

==J==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=jack}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#stressing jack|stressing jack]]''.}}

{{term|1=jack ram}}
{{defn|1=The active hydraulic cylinder of a stressing jack, being the cylinder that extends from the body of the jack as the tendon strain increases. }}

{{term|1=jacking force}}
{{defn|1=The prestressing force applied by the stressing jack to the tendons during tensioning.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|36}} }}
{{glossary end}}

