==L==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=lift-off load}}
{{defn|1=The force required to be applied to an already-tensioned anchor block to lift it free of its associated anchor or bearing plate. This value represents the magnitude of prestressing force within the tendon at that point in time.<ref name="PTI"/>{{rp|23}}}}

{{term|1=live end anchorage}}
{{defn|1=A "active end anchorage of a prestressing tendon that has jacking operations undertaken at that end.<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|20}}}}

{{term|1=load balancing}}
{{defn|1=A prestressed concrete design method in which the prestressing forces exerted upon the member act to balance a given proportion of the service loads that the member will be subjected to.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|38}} }}

{{term|1=longitudinal prestressing}}
{{defn|1=Prestressing forces acting along the longitudinal axis of the member.}}

{{term|1=low point}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon low point|tendon low point]]''.}}

{{glossary end}}

==M==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=Macalloy bar}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#threaded bar|threaded bar]]''. }}

{{term|1=measured extension}}
{{defn|1=The measured tendon elongation produced by tensioning operations on that tendon.}}

{{term|1=minimum prestress level}}
{{defn|1=The (generally long-term) minimum level of residual prestressing stress within a member following tensioning and the actions of all time-dependent losses.}}

{{term|1=mono-strand}}
{{defn|1=A prestressing system utilising tendons with single strands, or tendons able to be tensioned using a mono-strand jack.<ref name="PTI"/>{{rp|12}} }}

{{term|1=mono-strand jack}}
{{defn|1=A tensioning jack that applies force to a single tendon strand at a time. }}

{{term|1=multi-strand}}
{{defn|1=A prestressing system utilising tendons with multiple strands, and are tensioned using a multi-strand jack.<ref name="PTI"/>{{rp|13}} }}

{{term|1=multi-strand jack}}
{{defn|1=A tensioning jack that applies force to a more than one tendon strand at a time. }}
{{glossary end}}

