==O==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=offset}}
{{defn|1=The eccentricity within a post-tensioning tendon between the centreline of the duct component and the centreline of the strand bundle. }}

{{term|1=onion dead end}}
{{defn|1=A form of dead-end anchorage utilising strand "onions" or "bulbs" on the ends of each prestressing strand.<ref name="FIB31"/>{{rp|33}}}}
{{glossary end}}

==P==
{{glossary}}
{{term|1=P/A level}}
{{defn|1=The level of compressive stress present within an element due to prestressing forces. Derived from the prestressing force at that location divided by the cross-sectional area.}}

{{term|1=partial prestressing}}
{{defn|1=Prestressing to a stress level such that, under design loads, tensile stresses are allowed to exist in the pre-compressed tensile zone of the member. Can be compared to ''full prestressing''.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|45}}<ref name="LinTY"/>{{rp|325}} }}

{{term|1=preload}}
{{defn|1=A quantity of initial prestressing force applied to a tendon or structural element, prior to subsequent operations being undertaken. }}

{{term|1=pre-tensioning |2=[[Prestressed concrete#Pre-tensioned concrete|pre-tensioning]]}}
{{term|1=pre-tensioned|multi=y}}
{{defn|1=A method of prestressing concrete where the tendons are tensioned before the concrete is placed.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|51}} }}

{{term|1=post-tensioning |2=[[Prestressed concrete#Post-tensioned concrete|post-tensioning]]}}
{{term|1=post-tensioned|multi=y}}
{{defn|1=A method of prestressing concrete where the tendons are tensioned after the concrete has attained a specified minimum strength or age.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|50}} }}

{{term|1=prestress level}}
{{defn|1=The level of compressive stress created within a prestressed concrete member as a result of prestressing. }}

{{term|1=prestressing |2=[[Prestressed concrete]]}}
{{defn|1=The introduction of internal stresses into structural concrete via tensioned tendons, to reduce potential tensile stresses in the concrete from applied loads.<ref name="ACI"/>{{rp|51}} }}

{{term|1=primary grouting}}
{{defn|1=The first, or only, stage of grouting for post-tensioned tendons. Multiple stages of grouting may be employed for doubly-encapsulated tendons such as re-stressable ground anchors.}}

{{term|1=profile}}
{{defn|1=See ''[[#tendon profile|tendon profile]]''. }}

{{term|1=profiled tendon}}
{{defn|1=A tendon that has been draped or harped to give it a non-flat profile between end anchorages. }}

{{term|1=pump |2=[[Hydraulic pump|pump]]}}
{{defn|1=A device to provide hydraulic pressure for the operation of stressing jacks. Also a device to provide a supply of pressurised grout for the grouting of bonded tendons.}}

{{glossary end}}

